  "texts": [
    "Further, let the lower limit for LIT-101 be 10 mm; below which the PLC turns OFF the pump P-101; to prevent dry pumping.",
    "For the tank filling state MV101 = OPEN and P101 = OFF, the attacker would spoof the LIT101 value on the PLC toLevelval i = Levelval i + (δ • i); at each time step i = {1, 2, • • •,tmax} ∈ tsteps.This causes the water level to appear to be higher than it actually is.",
    "For the tank draining state MV101 = CLOSE and P101 = ON, the attacker would spoof the LIT101 value on the PLC to Levelval j = Levelval j + δ • (i + j); again, causing the tank to appear fuller than it is.",
    "By adjusting the value of δ and the number of time-steps i, it results in tank under-flow and P-101 dry pumping.",
    "For example, consider LIT-101 value is 12 mm."
  ],
